data.description: PRICE REDUCED AND NEW ROOF PRIOR TO CLOSING WITH GOOD OFFER!! Welcome to this charming historic Craftsman home, nestled in the heart of a vibrant neighborhood, built in 1920. Take a step back in time as you sip your morning coffee on the front porch swing. Step inside this warm and inviting home, where you will find three cozy bedrooms and a classic bathroom featuring a vintage clawfoot tub. The perfect retreat for relaxation and rest. Plumbing was updated in 20-21 when the bathroom was remodeled. The living room boasts a charming fireplace, adding even more character to the room . Step into your new dining room which is perfect for hosting dinner parties. Open or close the barn doors between the living room and dining room for extra privacy when needed. The kitchen features butcher block countertops and a window above the kitchen sink allows natural light to flow into the room. The fenced yard provides privacy and security, and there is even a storage shed with electricity. A huge driveway from the front to the rear of the property is great for parking an RV or boat being the privacy fence. This home is located in a convenient neighborhood just a few blocks from Lake Hollingsworth. This Craftsman home offers a unique opportunity to own a piece of history while enjoying modern comforts. With its convenient location, classic features, and versatile spaces, this property is sure to captivate your heart. Don’t miss the chance to make this charming historic Craftsman your new home!
